Usage: set_analysis_view [-help] [-drv <list_of_views>] [-dynamic <string>]
                         [-hold <list_of_views>] [-inactive <string>]
                         [-leakage <string>] [-setup <list_of_views>]
                         [-update_timing]

-help                      # Prints out the command usage
-drv <list_of_views>       # Sets views as drv views (string, optional)
-dynamic <string>          # Set a view as dynamic view (string, optional)
-hold <list_of_views>      # Sets the active views for hold analysis
                           # (string, optional)
-inactive <string>         # Set views inactive for timing analysis
                           # (string, optional)
-leakage <string>          # Set a view as leakage view (string, optional)
-setup <list_of_views>     # Sets the active views for setup analysis
                           # (string, optional)
-update_timing             # Reloads the configuration described by the MMMC
                           # view and mode objects (bool, optional)